disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from An Acquired Taste.

blurb.value: Tahm Kench puts the heft of his immense body behind his attacks and abilities, gaining extra damage based on his total health. Damaging enemy champions builds stacks of An Acquired Taste. At three stacks, he can use Devour on an enemy champion.

description.value: Innate: Tahm Kench's basic attacks deal 4% of his maximum health bonus magic damage. Against enemy champions they also apply An Acquired Taste stack for 5 seconds, stacking up to 3 times. The stacks decay once every 0.67 seconds after the stacks reach the full duration.

description2.value: Tongue Lash and Devour gain additional effects against enemies with three stacks.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value:
* By calculating An Acquired Taste's base damage, using Tahm Kench's base health, An Acquired Taste's damage can be acquired in a different way: 24 − 92 (based on level) (+ 4% bonus health) magic damage.
 The passive bonus damage applies to turrets.

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Tongue Lash.

blurb.value: Tahm Kench lashes out with his tongue, damaging and slowing the first unit hit. This ability gains a stun after three stacks of An Acquired Taste.

description.value: Active: Tahm Kench lashes his tongue in the target direction, dealing magic damage to the first enemy hit and slowing them for 3 seconds.

description2.value: If an enemy champion is struck while at three An Acquired Taste stacks, they're also stunned for 2 seconds, consuming all stacks.

description3.value: During Tongue Lash, Devour can be cast for no  mana expenditure to devour the minion or non-epic monster struck at the cost of no longer dealing Tongue Lash's damage. Devour's mana refund does not apply in this case.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Devour.

target range.value: 250

blurb.value: Tahm Kench devours a target, dealing a percentage of their maximum health as magic damage. He can spit devoured minions and monsters out as a skillshot that deals magic damage in an area upon impact.

description.value: Active: Tahm Kench swallows the target enemy minion, non-epic monster or allied champion for up to 4 seconds. Swallowed units are rendered untargetable and cannot perform any actions. If the target is an enemy, they are instantly stunned for 0.5 seconds and suppressed for the cast time and while swallowed.

description2.value: Tahm Kench can swallow a target enemy champion for up to 2 seconds if they have three An Acquired Taste stacks, doing so consumes all of them. If Tahm Kench swallows a champion, he becomes unable to cast movement spells and is slowed by 95% for the duration.

description3.value: Swallowing an enemy refunds 50% of Devour's  cooldown and  mana cost.

description4.value: After 1 second, Devour can be recast into Regurgitate while Tahm Kench's belly is full, and automatically does so at the end of the duration. Allied champions can exit at will after the same delay, unless they're immobilized.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Devour does not destroy in-flight projectiles for enemy targets. Devour renders enemies untargetable once they are inside Tahm Kench's belly. Allies become untargetable on-cast. Devour counts as an ability activation for the purposes of on-cast effects such as Spellblade, charging Spellbinder, and stacking Force Pulse. Detonating the ability early for Regurgitate does not. Devour's initial suppression is separate from the one that lasts while swallowed. If the target cleanses the initial one, they will become swallowed immediately. Devour will remove airborne effects from the target upon entering Tahm Kench's belly. Swallowed non-champions cannot be reduced below  1 health. Devour cannot be used on allies that are channeling. Devour cannot be cast on units that are displacement immune. Devour's cast will cancel if the target become displacement immune or immune to crowd control during the cast time. The  cooldown will be refunded if this occurs. Swallowed enemy champions will receive Regurgitate's damage immediately if they cleanse the suppression or Tahm Kench dies. Devour is canceled if the target dies during the cast time. It does not go on  cooldown nor expend  mana. The self-slow is affected by slow resist. Devour will prioritize champions over other units. If champions stay on top of each other it will prioritize those who stay beneath. Devour cannot be used on post-death forms such as Glory in Death or on targets that are already being devoured by another Tahm Kench. Devour will not interrupt persistent area-of-effect abilities (e.g. Crowstorm, Slicing Maelstrom, Inferno Trigger) nor non-channeled ones (e.g. Center of the Universe).

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Thick Skin.

blurb.value: Tahm Kench turns incoming damage into gray health. As gray health decays, Tahm Kench is healed for a percentage of the gray health amount. When activated, this ability turns all gray health into a shield.

description.value: Passive: Tahm Kench stores a percentage of the damage he takes as Grey Health on his health bar, up to a maximum of 100% of his missing health.

description2.value: While Thick Skin is available, and after taking no damage for 2.5 seconds, Tahm Kench rapidly heals for 30% − 100% (based on level) of his Grey Health over time.

description3.value: Active: Tahm Kench converts his current Grey Health into a shield that lasts for 2 seconds.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Thick Skin shield value and Grey Health percentage heal are both boosted by effects that increase heal and shield power. This means Tahm Kench can technically heal more than the normal amount of Grey Health and get a shield bigger than his maximum health. At level 18 Tahm Kench would need 53.8%  heal power to heal for 100% of the damage he takes, reduced to 39.9% with Revitalize, 18.3% with Spirit Visage, and 7.6% with both. Grey Health converts all post-mitigation damage, Thick Skin effectively grants Tahm Kench a form of true damage mitigation. Grey Health can temporarily exceed 100% of his missing health when Tahm Kench heals through other means with a Grey Health bar at 100%. In that case he will keep the higher Grey Health value for a few moments until it updates and removes the amount that he healed.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Abyssal Voyage.

blurb.value: Tahm Kench teleports across the map, and he may bring one ally champion with him.

description.value: Active: Tahm Kench channels for up to 6 seconds, highlighting the path to his intended destination to allied champions while opening his maw to offer up to one of them the chance to come with him. Abyssal Voyage can be recast 0.25 seconds after starting the channel. If an ally has climbed in, they immediately become untargetable and Tahm Kench automatically begins a 1.65-second channel that, when completed, renders Tahm Kench also untargetable and causes him and his ally to blink to the target location, both becoming unable to perform actions for 1 second and afterwards becoming targetable again.

description2.value: Recast: Tahm Kench manually begins the channel to blink to the target location. Allies can still join him while they have the chance during this time.

description3.value: Abyssal Voyage is put on a 10 second  cooldown if the second channel is not started or is interrupted.

description4.value: Allies must be out of combat with enemy champions to come with Tahm Kench. Tahm Kench may also not start the channel if he has Devoured someone.
